1 A RESOLUTION adjourning the Senate in honor and loving memory of Bobby F.
2 Crager.
3 WHEREAS, Bobby F. Crager was born in Prestonsburg, Kentucky, and called
4 Flatwoods, Kentucky, home for more than 55 years, becoming a pillar of the community
5 through his work as a public servant, educator, and leader, as well as a beloved friend,
6 devoted husband, dedicated father, proud grandfather, and cherished great-grandfather;
7 and
8 WHEREAS, Bobby F. Crager served his country honorably in the United States Air
9 Force from 1956 to 1960, exemplifying his commitment to his country, and later devoted
10 26 years to the Flatwoods City Council, and held the distinction of being the longest-
11 serving mayor in the city's history, working every day to improve the lives of the
12 community of Flatwoods, leaving a lasting impact on the city he so highly revered; and
13 WHEREAS, in addition to his public service, Bobby F. Crager was a founding
14 member of the Flatwoods Lions Club, for which he dedicated his time as treasurer, and
15 where he worked to support projects, charities, and initiatives that helped develop and
16 strengthen the community; and
17 WHEREAS, Bobby F. Crager was a beloved biology teacher and a remarkable
18 football coach at Prestonsburg High School, and later served in the Russell Independent
19 School System as the principal of McDowell Elementary School; and
20 WHEREAS, Bobby F. Crager was a faithful servant of the Lord, held various
21 leadership roles in the church community, and was a Sunday School teacher at Advance
22 Methodist Church in Flatwoods, Kentucky, where he inspired the community through his
23 kindness, faith, and leadership; and
24 WHEREAS, Bobby F. Crager was preceded in death by his parents, Woodrow and
25 Marietta Bingham Crager; his brother, James Buford Crager; and his sister, Barbara Lynn
26 Knicley Hoyle; and
27 WHEREAS, Bobby F. Crager is survived by his devoted wife of 61 years, Judith
