4 WHEREAS, Bobby F. Crager is further survived by his dear sister, Brenda (Jack)
5 Helton Davis; his sisters-in-law, Jenny Crager, Janet Hicks, and Brenda Porter; his
6 brother-in-law, Jeffrey Hicks; along with the loving faculty and staff of McDowell
7 Elementary School; and
8 WHEREAS, it is with great sorrow that we acknowledge the passing of Bobby F.
9 Crager, who departed this earthly life peacefully, surrounded by his loving family, on
10 February 14, 2025, at the age of 86, leaving behind a legacy of service, friendship, and
11 faith;
12 NOW, THEREFORE,
13 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
14 Kentucky:
15 Section 1. The Senate expresses its most profound sympathy upon the passing
16 of Bobby F. Crager and extends heartfelt condolences to all his family, friends, and
17 community.
18 Section 2. When the Senate adjourns this day, it does so in honor and loving
19 memory of Bobby F. Crager.
20 Section 3. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
21 Resolution to Senator Robin L. Webb for delivery to the family.
